description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;***Please note this is an INTERNAL VACANCY ONLY for NUH employees, therefore only current employees of Nottingham University Hospitals NHS Trust will be considered for the post.***&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deputy Ward Sister / Deputy Charge Nurse 30 hours &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Berman 2 Ward (formally Nightingale Ward) is looking to recruit an enthusiastic, self-motivated Registered Nurse to complement our existing team. Within the CAS division we have 13 beds and care for a variety of patients both male and female, of varying age ranges. As we specialise in infectious and tropical diseases and our patients come from diverse backgrounds communication and emotional intelligence is a prerequisite for this post. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The current Ward Manager is specifically looking for an individual whom is willing to undertake positive change and would be willing to work towards developing a specific learning pathway for you.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Berman 2 Ward is committed to providing the highest quality of care and maintaining consistent high standards in a professional and friendly atmosphere. We have an active Shared Governance Council and are focused on our Trusts Magnet journey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You in turn will be fully supported and have opportunity to influence future nursing practise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applicants should be:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• 1st level registered nurse/degree in health nursing related studies.&lt;br /&gt;• Have 2 years post registration experience &lt;br /&gt;• Infectious Diseases Experience (desirable) &lt;br /&gt;• Be willing to develop personally and professionally &lt;br /&gt;• Be willing to undertake the CAS band 6 development course.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• A clinical role model &lt;br /&gt;• Evidence of undertaking appraisals (desirable)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you are committed to being the best we would like to hear from you.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name-Yvette Milnes&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title-Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address-yvette.milnes@nuh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number-72166 or 73299&lt;/p&gt;
